            <scopecontent id="aspace_30ba21f5fa74b28503a523e2e5e47896">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The records are divided into 3 parts. Part I consists of mimeographed flyers from the United Office and Professional Workers of America Union who were trying to organize a union within the University Libraries during 1946 and 1947. Part II contains Yale Non-Faculty Action Committee (YNFAC) flyers and newsletters and University memos regarding the union. This union was actively recruiting library workers from 1969 through 1972. Part III is made up of flyers from the Yale Employees Society (YES), Office and Professional Employees International Union (OPEIU), Technical, Office, Professional (TOP) and United Auto Workers (UAW) Local 1701, together with University memos about University policy regarding unions.</p>
            </scopecontent>
